The paper deals with algorithms for computing average distances in graphs and metric spaces, which are fundamental problems in data analysis. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of weighted sampling, which is a common technique in machine learning and statistics, indicating that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Statistical Learning (cs.SI). The paper also presents algorithms with statistical guarantees, which could place it in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and network analysis, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
